-- Colombian Stocks: Sura, Banco Davivienda, Isagen Were Active
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-05-16T22:38:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/colombian-stocks-sura-banco-davivienda-isagen-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.3 percent to 14,535.49 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  climbed 0.2 percent to 1,737.27.  MSCI Inc. added  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR) , Banco
Davivienda SA and  Isagen (ISAGEN)  SA to its Colombia and Latin America
indexes, driving gains in the shares. MSCI didn’t remove any
Colombian securities from the index, according to the statement
on MSCI’s website dated yesterday.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana  (GRUPOSUR CB), Latin
America’s largest private pension-fund manager, added 0.8
percent to 31,680 pesos.  Banco Davivienda  (PFDAVVND) (PFDAVVND CB), Colombia’s third-biggest
bank, jumped 5.5 percent to 22,100 pesos.  Isagen (ISAGEN CB), a Colombian energy company, rose 2.1
percent to 2,430 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  